review_blob: Enjoyed this sweet elixir at the Montreal Beer Festival 2010. Strong sweet tummy beer. Maybe my favorite of the festival.
I enjoyed this Belgium strong ale at MaHaffeys Pub in Baltimore.  This beer was a sweet, fruity, and malty beer. Nice dark color. Very easy drinking. I think I will have another.

Great seasonal beer which has been reborn from the old version to pack a new powerful punch.  This beer has a very pronounced coffee flavor, due to the use of sematra coffee beans. I was one of the lucky few which were able to enjoy this beer on cask at MaHaffeys pub in Baltimore. The cask was pushing neat the 10% mark. I enjoyed several beers which gave me a nice coffee buzz.
A dark rich stout that is full of flavo. This is a very easy drinking stout, smooth to the last drop. Sweet with chocolate and coffee hint.  This one I will drink again.
great citrus flavor, good to the last drop. my favorite avery beer yet.  not exactly what i expect in a saison, but i do love the beer

2002 vintage, consumed on dec 6, must admit I consumed 2 bottles which gave me a smile I wont soon forget. The first bottle was cunsumed at 50F out of a standard Unibroue glass. The aroma just about knocked me off my barstool. Taste of cherries and spices with very little alcohol taste(for an 8% beer). One of the best beer I have ever had. BUT WAIT!!!! There was the second bottle in which Chef Frankie(at MaHaffeys Pub), dropped the bottle into a pale of simmering water. When the nectar of cherries reached 100F, we sampled something that was ment to be sample by the best of the gods. This was hot cherry cobbler that mom would be proud of. This was quite simply the best thing i have ever drank. Chef Freddy and just stared at each other, smiled and nodded. No word necessary. Enjoy this with the family at christmas, I know i will!

bottle/ the woody taste and the lingering aftertaste that does not disapate is quite exquist. the deep color is nice. the nose is quite different(but good) due to the wiskey malts. this is what makes unibroue one of the best brewerys in the world

A well done tart belgium lambic. For most beer drinkers it will be a little on the sour side. For more experienced beer drinkers it will be on the exquisite side. Its worth a drink for you Belgium lovers.
2004/bottle, very strong but drinkable beer. one that I will cherish. It is a triple with spice, how nice. A must for christmas beer drinkers. Pink elephants are to die for.
ordinary beer, nothing special. this is a beer you could drink in place of american budwiser.
One of my most favorite beer. A must for those who like triples. Avery drinkable beer for the ABV.
Had it on tap very enjoyable, great citrus taste. Super hoppy. Its one of the better IPAs on the market
